<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued April 12 at 8:30PM CDT until April 12 at 9:00PM CDT by NWS Topeka</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 900 PM CDT
FOR NORTHWESTERN RILEY...NORTHERN CLAY AND SOUTHEASTERN CLOUD
COUNTIES...
At 830 PM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 3 miles south of Palmer to 3 miles southwest of Idana,
moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage to
roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Clay Center, Clifton, Miltonvale, Leonardville, Morganville, Green,
Vining and Idana.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
